# donatingInteraction

**Type Property**

The [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INInteraction] object could not be donated to the system.

## Declaration

```swift
static var donatingInteraction: INIntentError.Code { get }
```

## Discussion

To determine the low-level cause of the problem, check the value of [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Foundation/NSUnderlyingErrorKey] in the error object’s [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Foundation/NSError/userInfo] dictionary.

## Interaction Errors

- **interactionOperationNotSupported**: The [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INInteraction] object could not be donated or deleted because those capabilities are not supported on the current device.
- **deletingAllInteractions**: The system was unable to delete all donated [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INInteraction] objects.
- **deletingInteractionWithIdentifiers**: The system was unable to delete the specified set of [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INInteraction] objects.
- **deletingInteractionWithGroupIdentifier**: The system was unable to delete the [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INInteraction] objects using their group identifier.
